social_posts.post_text: Today marks 3 years since my accident. The day my life flipped upside down. I carry my battle scar with pride. I’m truly grateful for each and everyday I’m still here. It has given me the super human strength to power over these obstacles. I believe in myself. Through all the doubt. All the people that turned their back on me. The ones saying I’m not going to be able to tattoo again yet alone open a shop in LA. 🖕🏻here I am. I’m grateful and Im absorbing everything I learn along the way. I feel it in my bones that I have a purpose here. I’ve never been so ready in my life. The tattoos I create now are a symbol of resilience. Im giving it my everything. It’s been such a long, hard and lonely road for myself but that only drives me harder to reach the goals me and my day ones set out to achieve. Opening the best tattoo shop in my power on the other side of the country. A hub for the best of the best in the industry. I know my fallen soldiers are watching over me. I feel you guys and I embrace those moments. I took a break from social media for awhile and have been working every single day on this shop and it’s been the only thing keeping me going. Literally dumping my life into it. Blood, sweat and tears. Still a lot to go but I’m almost finished building @oxfordcircletattoo and it has been very bittersweet knowing the doors are almost ready to officially open 😩😭 This experience has taught me so much and I want you to know that anything is fucking possible.  For anyone reading this and struggling, YOU do have the willpower. YOU have a purpose. YOU can make your dreams a reality if you truly believe. Yell that shit into existence! You’ll be surprised what your capable of when your not given a choice. Love you guys and can’t wait to show you all what I’ve been building. The support means  more to me than you know. My heart is very full today💚🧡🖤
